<h2 class="heading-subtitle">1) Sir Winston Churchill...again</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>1951-1955, Conservative</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">Although Winston Churchill had previously served as Prime Minister, it was during Queen Elizabeth&#x27;s father, King George VI&#x27;s reign.</p><p class="paragraph-text">The much-loved politician remains an icon of patriotism and strength, as he navigated the country through the war and reinforced a &quot;stiff upper lip&quot; attitude among the people.</p><p class="paragraph-text">In 1953, Churchill won the Nobel Prize for Literature, became a Knight of the Garter and was accorded a rare state funeral after his death in January 1965.</p>

<figure>
    
        <img
            loading="lazy"
            alt="Sir Anthony Eden was Prime Minister between 1955-1957"
