<h2 class="heading-subtitle">4) Alec Douglas-Home</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>1963-1964, Conservative</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">Despite only serving as Prime Minister for a total of 363 days, Douglas-Home managed to oversee the abolition of resale price maintenance and dealing with trade unions.</p>

