<figcaption>
    Gordon Brown was PM between 2007-2010.
    <span class=attribution>
        Picture: <a href="https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/license/96156403" target="_blank">
Getty
</a>

    </span>
</figcaption>

</figure>

<h2 class="heading-subtitle">11) Gordon Brown</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>2007-2010, Labour</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">Under Gordon Brown&#x27;s leadership, the withdrawal of British troops in Iraq began. He also oversaw the world&#x27;s first ever Climate Change Act and focused on the devolution of powers in Northern Ireland.</p>

<figure>
    
        <img
            loading="lazy"
            alt="David Cameron was Britain&#39;s PM from 2010-2016"
            class="content-image"
            data-image-catalogue-id="64394"
            width="660"
            height="370"
            src="https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64394?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=jMXh2KYOdKHEQuyKcqhMkIu-ono="
            srcset="
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64394?crop=16_9&amp;width=375&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=d8p-N_cm6ZsMGb6brTl7_5eO2xU= 375w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64394?crop=16_9&amp;width=420&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=LY2PHMw5-PLHLpZJZXY3gX9pt9c= 420w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64394?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=jMXh2KYOdKHEQuyKcqhMkIu-ono= 660w"
            sizes="
                (max-width: 375px) 375px,
                (max-width: 420px) 420px,
                660px"
        />
    
    
<figcaption>
    David Cameron was Britain&#39;s PM from 2010-2016.
    <span class=attribution>
        Picture: <a href="https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/license/531841114" target="_blank">
Getty
</a>

    </span>
</figcaption>

</figure>

<h2 class="heading-subtitle">12) David Cameron</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>2010-2016, Conservative</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">Beating Tony Blair&#x27;s record, <a href="/politics/parties/conservatives/david-cameron/">David Cameron</a> became the youngest Prime Minister since 1812.</p><p class="paragraph-text">After the 2010 General Election, which resulted in a <a href="/politics/elections/general-election-2017/what-is-a-hung-parliament-what-happens/">hung parliament</a>, Cameron formed a coalition government with the Lib Dems, led by Nick Clegg.</p><p class="paragraph-text">From the offset, Cameron made it clear he wanted to put political differences aside to come up with an action plan for the &quot;common good&quot;.</p><p class="paragraph-text">In response to the Great Recession, David Cameron reinforced an austerity policy, a deficit-reducing programme to reduce government spending. This led to major cuts in public sectors.</p><p class="paragraph-text">After calling a referendum on whether Britain should remain or leave the EU in 2016, Cameron resigned as PM.</p>

<figure>
    
        <img
            loading="lazy"
            alt="Theresa May served between 2016-2019"
            class="content-image"
            data-image-catalogue-id="64396"
            width="660"
            height="370"
            src="https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64396?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=pK6J3ecq7ZMjNCfCdzcIQa1iHhM="
            srcset="
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64396?crop=16_9&amp;width=375&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=CsF76OIAbwZh1eCtpKsqEE5FR2M= 375w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64396?crop=16_9&amp;width=420&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=XTRQOD5bbQhUHH9SrYMOFNY0bxQ= 420w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/64396?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=pK6J3ecq7ZMjNCfCdzcIQa1iHhM= 660w"
            sizes="
                (max-width: 375px) 375px,
                (max-width: 420px) 420px,
                660px"
        />
    
    
<figcaption>
    Theresa May served between 2016-2019.
    <span class=attribution>
        Picture: <a href="https://www.gettyimages.co.uk/license/612803526" target="_blank">
Getty
</a>

    </span>
</figcaption>

</figure>

<h2 class="heading-subtitle">13) Theresa May</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>2016-2019, Conservative</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">The most prominent factor of May&#x27;s career is her implementation of <a href="/hot-topics/brexit/">Brexit</a> and her <a href="/news/uk/man-behind-theresa-mays-brexit-deal-to-quit-a/">negotiations with the European Unio</a>n on the UK&#x27;s exit - or lack there of. </p>

<figure>
    
        <img
            loading="lazy"
            alt="Boris Johnson as PM"
            class="content-image"
            data-image-catalogue-id="325725"
            width="660"
            height="370"
            src="https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/325725?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=WqziS8oYXfBexa04JJX2OSehUVI="
            srcset="
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/325725?crop=16_9&amp;width=375&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=nHLkX3FwXfca8J7vyfsQAcZ3Esw= 375w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/325725?crop=16_9&amp;width=420&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=hUdJ0tr90x41ShCjdFAKASZOcB0= 420w,
                https://images.lbc.co.uk/images/325725?crop=16_9&amp;width=660&amp;relax=1&amp;format=webp&amp;signature=WqziS8oYXfBexa04JJX2OSehUVI= 660w"
            sizes="
                (max-width: 375px) 375px,
                (max-width: 420px) 420px,
                660px"
        />
    
    
<figcaption>
    Boris Johnson stepped down as prime minister in July 2022.
    <span class=attribution>
        Picture: 
Alamy


    </span>
</figcaption>

</figure>

<h2 class="heading-subtitle">14) Boris Johnson</h2><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>2019-2022, Conservative</strong></p><p class="paragraph-text">Boris Johnson had one of the biggest success stories of the Conservative party to secure his leadership, however, he fell hard when he lost the trust of some of his closest MPs. He also fell out of favour with the public following the Partygate scandal which saw him break coronavirus lockdown laws.</p>

<figure>
    
        <img
            loading="lazy"
            alt="Liz Truss delivering a speech"
            class="content-image"
            data-image-catalogue-id="325724"
            width="660"
            height="370"
